.UPDATE...
Issued at 908 AM PST Wed Mar 4 2026

High clouds associated with a dry cold front have moved southeast
of Monterey County into the southern Central Coast and the San
Joaquin Valley. Behind the front, low clouds across the bay Area
and parts of the Monterey Bay are expected to dissipate through
the morning, but are not expected to return tonight as strong
winds aloft will promote low level mixing and inhibit stratus
development. Strong northwest winds are expected to develop this
afternoon with the gusty conditions continuing through the next
couple of days, as the wind direction gradually shifts to the
northeast by late Friday into Saturday. Wind gusts of 30 to 40 mph
have already been reported at some of the highest peaks and the
exposed coastal areas.

